{"metadata": {"page_hash": "09686dce5bfbe9aab8ca9afc7c7926731801fd640d66f70b200b9f86b18a2231", "original_filename": "1410.8736.pdf", "page_no": 1, "num_pages": 11, "original_width": 612, "original_height": 792, "coco_width": 1025, "coco_height": 1025, "collection": "arxiv_doublespaced", "doc_category": "scientific_articles"}, "form": [{"id_box": 297767, "box": [198.22696078431372, 104.51500505050512, 139.7530053104575, 11.449457070707012], "id_box_line": 0, "box_line": [198.22696078431372, 104.51500505050512, 14.907017156862764, 11.449457070707012], "text": "1.", "category": "Section-header", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/DERNEF+CMBX10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297767, "box": [198.22696078431372, 104.51500505050512, 139.7530053104575, 11.449457070707012], "id_box_line": 1, "box_line": [232.3058827614379, 104.51500505050512, 105.6740833333333, 11.449457070707012], "text": "Introduction", "category": "Section-header", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/DERNEF+CMBX10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297768, "box": [198.22684354575165, 137.51563068181827, 630.7371834150326, 398.33535763888887], "id_box_line": 2, "box_line": [198.22696078431372, 137.51563068181827, 630.7306180555555, 11.449457070707126], "text": "Silicon nitride-based waveguides form a promising, CMOS-compatible platform in inte-", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297768, "box": [198.22684354575165, 137.51563068181827, 630.7371834150326, 398.33535763888887], "id_box_line": 3, "box_line": [198.22696078431372, 163.30760732323233, 630.7332308006536, 11.449457070707126], "text": "grated photonics research [1]. Especially, stoichiometric silicon nitride (Si$_{3}$N$_{4}$) deposited", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297768, "box": [198.22684354575165, 137.51563068181827, 630.7371834150326, 398.33535763888887], "id_box_line": 4, "box_line": [198.22694403594772, 189.09957102272733, 630.7307352941177, 11.449470012626307], "text": "using low-pressure chemical vapor deposition (LPCVD) offers extremely low intrinsic", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297768, "box": [198.22684354575165, 137.51563068181827, 630.7371834150326, 398.33535763888887], "id_box_line": 5, "box_line": [198.22694403594772, 214.89281597222225, 630.7324268790851, 11.449457070707126], "text": "losses and superior reproducibility. Further advantages of this platform are a broad", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297768, "box": [198.22684354575165, 137.51563068181827, 630.7371834150326, 398.33535763888887], "id_box_line": 6, "box_line": [198.22694403594772, 240.68477967171725, 630.7309027777778, 11.449457070707126], "text": "transparency ranging from the visible [2] to the mid-infrared, a high index contrast", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297768, "box": [198.22684354575165, 137.51563068181827, 630.7371834150326, 398.33535763888887], "id_box_line": 7, "box_line": [198.22694403594772, 266.47675631313143, 630.7207197712419, 11.449457070707012], "text": "and absence of two-photon absorption in the near-infrared, including all the telecom-", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297768, "box": [198.22684354575165, 137.51563068181827, 630.7371834150326, 398.33535763888887], "id_box_line": 8, "box_line": [198.22694403594772, 292.26998832070717, 630.7340179738562, 11.449457070706899], "text": "munication bands. Due to their low propagation losses in the C-band as well as their", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297768, "box": [198.22684354575165, 137.51563068181827, 630.7371834150326, 398.33535763888887], "id_box_line": 9, "box_line": [198.22694403594772, 318.06196496212124, 630.7288594771242, 11.449457070707012], "text": "low coupling losses by using spot-size converters Si$_{3}$N$_{4}$ waveguides are favored in the", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297768, "box": [198.22684354575165, 137.51563068181827, 630.7371834150326, 398.33535763888887], "id_box_line": 10, "box_line": [198.22691053921568, 343.85392866161624, 630.7288427287583, 11.449470012626307], "text": "field of microwave photonics [3, 4] and for novel types (glass-semiconductor) lasers with", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297768, "box": [198.22684354575165, 137.51563068181827, 630.7371834150326, 398.33535763888887], "id_box_line": 11, "box_line": [198.22691053921568, 369.6472124368687, 630.7241364379086, 11.44941824494947], "text": "record low spectral bandwidth [5, 6]. Furthermore, ultra-low propagation losses in the", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297768, "box": [198.22684354575165, 137.51563068181827, 630.7371834150326, 398.33535763888887], "id_box_line": 12, "box_line": [198.22691053921568, 395.4391761363637, 630.7238684640524, 11.44941824494947], "text": "C-band of 0.32 dB/m have been demonstrated with weakly confined modes using 40 nm", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297768, "box": [198.22684354575165, 137.51563068181827, 630.7371834150326, 398.33535763888887], "id_box_line": 13, "box_line": [198.22691053921568, 421.2324210858586, 630.7239354575163, 11.44941824494947], "text": "thin Si$_{3}$N$_{4}$ waveguides [7, 8]. The low confinement of the mode, however, has the draw-", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297768, "box": [198.22684354575165, 137.51563068181827, 630.7371834150326, 398.33535763888887], "id_box_line": 14, "box_line": [198.22691053921568, 447.0243847853536, 630.7257107843138, 11.44941824494947], "text": "back of increased bending losses and, as a consequence, limit the density of devices", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297768, "box": [198.22684354575165, 137.51563068181827, 630.7371834150326, 398.33535763888887], "id_box_line": 15, "box_line": [198.22691053921568, 472.8163614267677, 630.7371164215685, 11.44941824494947], "text": "in integrated circuits. Further applications of Si$_{3}$N$_{4}$ waveguides are, e.g., bio-chemical", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297768, "box": [198.22684354575165, 137.51563068181827, 630.7371834150326, 398.33535763888887], "id_box_line": 16, "box_line": [198.22684354575165, 498.6095934343434, 630.7206192810457, 11.449418244949584], "text": "applications such as optical coherence tomography [9] and lab-on-a-chip devices due to", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297768, "box": [198.22684354575165, 137.51563068181827, 630.7371834150326, 398.33535763888887], "id_box_line": 17, "box_line": [198.22684354575165, 524.4015700757576, 535.1886429738562, 11.449418244949527], "text": "the compatibility of Si$_{3}$N$_{4}$ waveguides with microfluidic channels [10, 11].", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297769, "box": [198.22687704248366, 550.1935337752526, 630.7425093954248, 295.1661051136363], "id_box_line": 18, "box_line": [214.91325735294117, 550.1935337752526, 614.040234885621, 11.44941824494947], "text": "Furthermore, Si$_{3}$N$_{4}$ waveguides are of high interest for nonlinear integrated photon-", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297769, "box": [198.22687704248366, 550.1935337752526, 630.7425093954248, 295.1661051136363], "id_box_line": 19, "box_line": [198.22687704248366, 575.9867787247475, 630.727335375817, 11.44941824494947], "text": "ics [1] due to their high Kerr index [12], while supporting highly confined modes due", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297769, "box": [198.22687704248366, 550.1935337752526, 630.7425093954248, 295.1661051136363], "id_box_line": 20, "box_line": [198.22687704248366, 601.7787424242424, 630.7425093954248, 11.449418244949584], "text": "to their high index contrast and lacking nonlinear losses in the near-infrared. Nonlinear", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297769, "box": [198.22687704248366, 550.1935337752526, 630.7425093954248, 295.1661051136363], "id_box_line": 21, "box_line": [198.22687704248366, 627.5707190656566, 630.7322928921568, 11.44941824494947], "text": "effects such as supercontinuum generation [13] and parametric frequency comb gener-", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297769, "box": [198.22687704248366, 550.1935337752526, 630.7425093954248, 295.1661051136363], "id_box_line": 22, "box_line": [198.22687704248366, 653.3639510732323, 630.7405665849674, 11.44941824494947], "text": "ation [14] have been demonstrated. For the latter, huge potential in nonlinear optical", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297769, "box": [198.22687704248366, 550.1935337752526, 630.7425093954248, 295.1661051136363], "id_box_line": 23, "box_line": [198.22687704248366, 679.1559277146465, 630.7357598039215, 11.44941824494947], "text": "signal processing was shown by transmitting a data stream of 1.44 Tbit/s [15]. It is desir-", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297769, "box": [198.22687704248366, 550.1935337752526, 630.7425093954248, 295.1661051136363], "id_box_line": 24, "box_line": [198.22687704248366, 704.9478525883839, 630.7355588235295, 11.449444128787889], "text": "able to select the waveguides such that the pump wavelength for broadband wavelength", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297769, "box": [198.22687704248366, 550.1935337752526, 630.7425093954248, 295.1661051136363], "id_box_line": 25, "box_line": [198.22687704248366, 730.741110479798, 630.7307017973856, 11.449444128787889], "text": "conversion lies in the spectral region where laser sources are readily available, i.e. 1000", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297769, "box": [198.22687704248366, 550.1935337752526, 630.7425093954248, 295.1661051136363], "id_box_line": 26, "box_line": [198.22687704248366, 756.5330612373738, 630.7289767156863, 11.449444128787889], "text": "to 2000 nm. However, to obtain phase matching for broadband wavelength conversion,", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297769, "box": [198.22687704248366, 550.1935337752526, 630.7425093954248, 295.1661051136363], "id_box_line": 27, "box_line": [198.22687704248366, 782.3250119949495, 630.7255433006536, 11.449444128787889], "text": "the dispersion of the waveguide must be engineered such that pump wavelength is in the", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297769, "box": [198.22687704248366, 550.1935337752526, 630.7425093954248, 295.1661051136363], "id_box_line": 28, "box_line": [198.22687704248366, 808.1182440025252, 630.7389419934641, 11.449444128787889], "text": "anomalous dispersion regime, while also being close to the zero dispersion wavelength", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297769, "box": [198.22687704248366, 550.1935337752526, 630.7425093954248, 295.1661051136363], "id_box_line": 29, "box_line": [198.22687704248366, 833.9102077020202, 57.18866911764704, 11.44943118686868], "text": "(ZDW).", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}, {"id_box": 297770, "box": [214.9132741013072, 859.7034526515151, 614.0366004901962, 11.449444128787889], "id_box_line": 30, "box_line": [214.9132741013072, 859.7034526515151, 614.0366004901962, 11.449444128787889], "text": "To achieve high modal confinement and to shift the ZDW to the near-infrared, the", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/MJRJAG+CMR10", "size": 9.962599754333496}}]}